      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Draw a skeletal structure of the following carbocation. Identify it as primary, secondary, or tertiary, and identify the hydrogen atoms that have the proper orientation for hyperconjugation in the conformation shown.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBc2NSIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--94a023f74877e829979e16c91305505139af5643/OChem_07_09_007.jpg\" alt=\"A ball-and-stick model of 2-methylbutane. C 3 has only three bonds total.\">",
